            <ol>

                <li class="a">What is CSS3?</li>
                <a href="https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/difference-between-css-and-css3/" target="_blank">Related Link</a>
                <ul>
                    CSS3 is the latest version of the Cascading
                     Style Sheets (CSS) language. 
                     It is used to style and format web pages,
                      and it includes many new features and
                       improvements over CSS2.</ul>
                <li class="b">CSS Using Methods</li>
                <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/css/css_howto.asp" target="_blank"> W3 Schools <Link:touch></Link:touch></a>
                <ul>CSS basic selectors are used to target HTML
                     elements on a web page. There are three main
                      types of basic selectors:<br/>
                      <li>Element Selectors</li>
                      <li>Class Selectors</li>
                      <li>ID Selectors</li>                   
                    </ul>
                <li class="c">Hierarchy</li>
                <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/css/css_comments.asp" target="_blank">W3 Schools Link</a>
                <ul>CSS3 hierarchy refers to the order in
                     which CSS rules are applied to HTML elements.
                      When there are multiple CSS rules 
                      that match a single HTML element,
                       the rule with the highest specificity
                        will be applied.</ul>
                <li class="d">Web Development Tool</li>
                <a href="https://developer.chrome.com/docs/devtools/" target="_blank">Chrome Link</a>
                <ul>
                    A web development tool is a software
                     application that helps developers create
                      and maintain websites. Web development tools
                       can be used for a variety of tasks, such as:</ul>
                       <ul>
                        <li>Writing and editing HTML, CSS, and JavaScript code
                            <li>Debugging code and identifying errors
                                <li>Optimizing websites for performance and accessibility
                                    <li>Deploying websites to production servers
                        </li>
                       </ul>
